@genzy_auth_HostAddress = https://localhost:7000
@accessToken = your-jwt-token-here
@refreshToken = your-refresh-token-here

### Register New User
POST {{genzy_auth_HostAddress}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123!",
  "fullName": "John Doe"
}

### Login with Email/Password
POST {{genzy_auth_HostAddress}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123!"
}

### External Login - Google
POST {{genzy_auth_HostAddress}}/auth/external-login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "provider": "Google",
  "token": "google-id-token-from-frontend"
}

### External Login - Facebook
POST {{genzy_auth_HostAddress}}/auth/external-login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "provider": "Facebook",
  "token": "facebook-access-token-from-frontend"
}

### Refresh Access Token
POST {{genzy_auth_HostAddress}}/auth/refresh-token
Content-Type: application/json

"{{refreshToken}}"

### Get Current User (Protected)
GET {{genzy_auth_HostAddress}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Logout (Revoke Refresh Token)
POST {{genzy_auth_HostAddress}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

"{{refreshToken}}"

### Revoke Token
POST {{genzy_auth_HostAddress}}/auth/revoke-token
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

"{{refreshToken}}"

### Google OAuth Flow (Browser)
# Open this URL in browser to test Google login flow
